>> Lisa: This is -- you're of
course teaching about tuning in

00:39:38.342 --> 00:39:40.111 align:middle line:90%
and going with the flow and all

00:39:40.111 --> 00:39:42.146 align:middle line:84%
of that you did while
you were on your journey.

00:39:42.146 --> 00:39:43.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Yes.

00:39:43.380 --> 00:39:44.782 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And I just feel
the need to ask you so much

00:39:44.782 --> 00:39:48.219 align:middle line:84%
about this pilgrimage
because it takes such a leap

00:39:48.219 --> 00:39:50.488 align:middle line:90%
of faith to go and to do.

00:39:50.488 --> 00:39:52.056 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Yes, it did.

00:39:52.056 --> 00:39:56.127 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: But it also has
to have a really big why.

00:39:56.127 --> 00:39:57.228 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Not for me.

00:39:57.228 --> 00:39:58.429 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: No?

00:39:58.429 --> 00:40:02.933 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: See, when
I, living by my guidance,

00:40:02.933 --> 00:40:05.770 align:middle line:90%
why is an intellectual question,

00:40:05.770 --> 00:40:09.974 align:middle line:84%
and I don't listen
to my intellect much.

00:40:09.974 --> 00:40:13.043 align:middle line:90%
I just said okay, and had no --

00:40:13.043 --> 00:40:14.845 align:middle line:84%
and that's pretty
much how I live.

00:40:14.845 --> 00:40:16.947 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Have you always
known about the Camino?

00:40:16.947 --> 00:40:18.349 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: No.

00:40:18.349 --> 00:40:22.420 align:middle line:84%
I had read -- a long time ago,
I read Shirley Maclean's book,

00:40:22.420 --> 00:40:24.989 align:middle line:90%
and thought, all right.

00:40:24.989 --> 00:40:30.227 align:middle line:84%
You know, it didn't -- it
wasn't something that stuck.

00:40:30.227 --> 00:40:33.631 align:middle line:84%
I enjoyed it, but it
wasn't -- so -- and then...

00:40:33.631 --> 00:40:34.632 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: What was her book?

00:40:34.632 --> 00:40:35.266 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: The Camino.

00:40:35.266 --> 00:40:36.567 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh, okay.

00:40:36.567 --> 00:40:39.837 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: So then two or
three people in the course

00:40:39.837 --> 00:40:43.707 align:middle line:84%
of the maybe year and a
half before I went had shown

00:40:43.707 --> 00:40:45.342 align:middle line:90%
up in my life in various places.

00:40:45.342 --> 00:40:49.780 align:middle line:84%
One in Australia, one in
Chicago, and I'm not sure

00:40:49.780 --> 00:40:52.216 align:middle line:84%
where the third, and they said,
"You have to go on the Camino."

00:40:52.216 --> 00:40:58.989 align:middle line:84%
And it was like, I do, but
I didn't really say I will.

00:40:58.989 --> 00:41:00.257 align:middle line:90%
It was like okay.

00:41:00.257 --> 00:41:01.725 align:middle line:90%
That feels right.

00:41:01.725 --> 00:41:03.494 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Oh, so your
intuition said yes.

00:41:03.494 --> 00:41:04.762 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: So
then I went speaking

00:41:04.762 --> 00:41:08.899 align:middle line:84%
at the first global conference
on human spirituality,

00:41:08.899 --> 00:41:11.702 align:middle line:84%
and I was very conflicted
why I was there.

00:41:11.702 --> 00:41:15.506 align:middle line:84%
I was in so much personal
turmoil, and I spoke,

00:41:15.506 --> 00:41:17.942 align:middle line:84%
and I got to the airport
and sat in my seat,

00:41:17.942 --> 00:41:23.147 align:middle line:84%
and I clicked my buckle,
and I heard it so loud,

00:41:23.147 --> 00:41:26.650 align:middle line:90%
"Walk the Camino, and go alone."

00:41:26.650 --> 00:41:30.287 align:middle line:90%
And I went, okay, okay.

00:41:30.287 --> 00:41:34.792 align:middle line:84%
So I went home, and that
was in December, a year ago,

00:41:34.792 --> 00:41:39.597 align:middle line:84%
and I said to my
business partner Ryan,

00:41:39.597 --> 00:41:41.332 align:middle line:90%
I'm going on a pilgrimage.

00:41:41.332 --> 00:41:45.636 align:middle line:84%
And he thought I was crazy
because I had just --

00:41:45.636 --> 00:41:50.107 align:middle line:84%
I was taking kickboxing to try
to move some of my own energy

00:41:50.107 --> 00:41:52.042 align:middle line:84%
in a different way and
some of my frustrations,

00:41:52.042 --> 00:41:53.777 align:middle line:90%
and I'd broken my knee.

00:41:53.777 --> 00:41:55.079 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Ow.

00:41:55.079 --> 00:41:56.247 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: And I was just
coming out of a wheelchair

00:41:56.247 --> 00:41:59.950 align:middle line:84%
after five months in a
wheelchair, so he said,

00:41:59.950 --> 00:42:03.454 align:middle line:84%
"You're going to walk five
hundred and some miles

00:42:03.454 --> 00:42:05.256 align:middle line:84%
across a country
with your knee?"

00:42:05.256 --> 00:42:08.959 align:middle line:90%
And I said, "I'm going to try.

00:42:08.959 --> 00:42:12.930 align:middle line:84%
I've got the guidance
to do that, so I'm going

00:42:12.930 --> 00:42:15.933 align:middle line:90%
to do it, and we'll see."

00:42:15.933 --> 00:42:18.836 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I
live with guidance.

00:42:18.836 --> 00:42:20.871 align:middle line:90%
I don't ask many questions.

00:42:20.871 --> 00:42:22.539 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: You trust it that much.

00:42:22.539 --> 00:42:23.974 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: I trust
it absolutely.

00:42:23.974 --> 00:42:24.975 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:42:24.975 --> 00:42:27.811 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: And
it's never, ever,

00:42:27.811 --> 00:42:30.481 align:middle line:90%
ever been a problem for me.

00:42:30.481 --> 00:42:31.148 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Never wrong.

00:42:31.148 --> 00:42:32.116 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Never.

00:42:32.116 --> 00:42:33.951 align:middle line:84%
Years ago I was told
to go to France,

00:42:33.951 --> 00:42:35.719 align:middle line:90%
and I had $500 in my pocket.

00:42:35.719 --> 00:42:38.122 align:middle line:84%
I got the guidance to
go to France and ended

00:42:38.122 --> 00:42:41.058 align:middle line:84%
up with a five year
scholarship to the Sorbonne.

00:42:41.058 --> 00:42:42.159 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:42:42.159 --> 00:42:43.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: It works
out, and my point is

00:42:43.460 --> 00:42:45.930 align:middle line:90%
that that's not exclusive to me.

00:42:45.930 --> 00:42:52.703 align:middle line:84%
The universe is that generous
if you'll just say yes.

00:42:52.703 --> 00:42:55.606 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: But you've been doing
this for 40 years with guides

00:42:55.606 --> 00:42:58.509 align:middle line:84%
and working with your
intuition and teaching about it.

00:42:58.509 --> 00:43:00.344 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Well, you
know, Lisa, it's like this.

00:43:00.344 --> 00:43:04.648 align:middle line:84%
It's not like you have
to build the Taj Mahal.

00:43:04.648 --> 00:43:06.317 align:middle line:84%
You just have to
turn on the light,

00:43:06.317 --> 00:43:07.952 align:middle line:90%
and it's hardwired in you.

00:43:07.952 --> 00:43:09.186 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: You just
start somewhere.

00:43:09.186 --> 00:43:12.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: So I teach
people to turn on the light,

00:43:12.690 --> 00:43:16.961 align:middle line:84%
and it works, so it's
not a matter of you

00:43:16.961 --> 00:43:19.797 align:middle line:84%
to create a relationship
with it to work.

00:43:19.797 --> 00:43:22.766 align:middle line:84%
You begin to create a dynamic
so you have enough experience

00:43:22.766 --> 00:43:26.971 align:middle line:84%
that you think this works,
and you feel so good.

00:43:26.971 --> 00:43:32.610 align:middle line:84%
Your whole energy expands,
so it's not a mental effort.

00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:35.245 align:middle line:84%
It's a -- you relax
into because it's

00:43:35.245 --> 00:43:36.547 align:middle line:90%
like putting a key in a lock.

00:43:36.547 --> 00:43:38.182 align:middle line:90%
It clicks; it opens.

00:43:38.182 --> 00:43:42.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So do you distinguish
that voice of your intuition

00:43:42.820 --> 00:43:48.892 align:middle line:84%
from maybe just a hunch
or something that you...

00:43:48.892 --> 00:43:51.295 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Wishful
thinking, for example?

00:43:51.295 --> 00:43:52.696 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah, right.

00:43:52.696 --> 00:43:54.732 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Well, when I teach
to listen to their intuition,

00:43:54.732 --> 00:43:58.869 align:middle line:84%
one of the tools that
I have is so essential.

00:43:58.869 --> 00:44:00.871 align:middle line:84%
Every time you get a
gut feeling, a hunch,

00:44:00.871 --> 00:44:04.375 align:middle line:90%
an aha, say it out loud.

00:44:04.375 --> 00:44:05.643 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Okay.

00:44:05.643 --> 00:44:08.746 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Because intuition
comes up from the heart

00:44:08.746 --> 00:44:13.083 align:middle line:84%
to the throat to the
ear, and you can hear

00:44:13.083 --> 00:44:17.354 align:middle line:84%
if the vibration is
resonant with your essence.

00:44:17.354 --> 00:44:19.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: That's why it helps
so much to talk it out.

00:44:19.490 --> 00:44:20.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Right.

00:44:20.190 --> 00:44:21.925 align:middle line:90%
You can't actually be

00:44:21.925 --> 00:44:24.828 align:middle line:84%
as effective trying
to figure it out.

00:44:24.828 --> 00:44:26.397 align:middle line:90%
You won't succeed.

00:44:26.397 --> 00:44:27.231 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Too many
voices [laughter]?

00:44:27.231 --> 00:44:28.665 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Too many voices.

00:44:28.665 --> 00:44:31.101 align:middle line:84%
You won't be able to
distinguish, but the sound

00:44:31.101 --> 00:44:38.942 align:middle line:84%
of your own voice will let you
know, and that is hitting home,

00:44:38.942 --> 00:44:43.947 align:middle line:84%
ringing true, if it feels
correct for you in the moment.

00:44:43.947 --> 00:44:46.917 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And do you call your
intuition and information

00:44:46.917 --> 00:44:49.119 align:middle line:90%
from your guides the same thing?

00:44:49.119 --> 00:44:50.454 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: It's
the same channel.

00:44:50.454 --> 00:44:52.623 align:middle line:90%
It's your inner teacher.

00:44:52.623 --> 00:44:56.560 align:middle line:84%
It's like -- your intuition
is like the radio station,

00:44:56.560 --> 00:45:00.431 align:middle line:84%
just like Gaiam has a
station that broadcasts,

00:45:00.431 --> 00:45:04.468 align:middle line:84%
and so it's the station
that pulls in higher self,

00:45:04.468 --> 00:45:08.072 align:middle line:84%
your guides, your
angels, all broadcast

00:45:08.072 --> 00:45:12.342 align:middle line:84%
through this heart-based
station.

00:45:12.342 --> 00:45:17.448 align:middle line:84%
And so it opens a spectrum
of and a variety of guidance

00:45:17.448 --> 00:45:20.851 align:middle line:84%
that you can begin, just
like flavors in a recipe.

00:45:20.851 --> 00:45:24.121 align:middle line:84%
You can begin once you
start to become familiar.

00:45:24.121 --> 00:45:26.523 align:middle line:84%
You can start to
distinguish them.

00:45:26.523 --> 00:45:28.125 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So you said
earlier that to go

00:45:28.125 --> 00:45:33.497 align:middle line:84%
on the pilgrimage alone, when
you click that belt, why alone?

00:45:33.497 --> 00:45:36.533 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Well, at the time,
that would be if I had any kind

00:45:36.533 --> 00:45:40.571 align:middle line:84%
of a question, but I don't
pursue those questions.

00:45:40.571 --> 00:45:42.873 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know.

00:45:42.873 --> 00:45:46.143 align:middle line:84%
I would've preferred
-- my more human,

00:45:46.143 --> 00:45:48.746 align:middle line:84%
vulnerable Sonia would've
preferred to go with someone.

00:45:48.746 --> 00:45:51.014 align:middle line:84%
I'm a go with someone
kind of person.

00:45:51.014 --> 00:45:52.583 align:middle line:90%
I'm a middle child of seven.

00:45:52.583 --> 00:45:54.685 align:middle line:90%
I'm a hang in there.

00:45:54.685 --> 00:45:58.288 align:middle line:84%
But now I can see that
especially as an intuitive

00:45:58.288 --> 00:46:03.594 align:middle line:84%
and a sensitive, my energy
is often scanning and picking

00:46:03.594 --> 00:46:05.262 align:middle line:90%
up not just my own experience,

00:46:05.262 --> 00:46:07.331 align:middle line:84%
but the experience
of those around me.

00:46:07.331 --> 00:46:08.565 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right.

00:46:08.565 --> 00:46:11.568 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: So the wisdom
of go alone is genius.

00:46:11.568 --> 00:46:15.672 align:middle line:84%
I was able to tune into
exclusively my own energy,

00:46:15.672 --> 00:46:19.309 align:middle line:84%
and I -- that is not a
very common thing for me.

00:46:19.309 --> 00:46:20.511 align:middle line:90%
I'm always picking up.

00:46:20.511 --> 00:46:21.645 align:middle line:90%
That's my work.

00:46:21.645 --> 00:46:22.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right.

00:46:22.980 --> 00:46:24.915 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: That is my life
to pick up and tune clear

00:46:24.915 --> 00:46:30.020 align:middle line:84%
across the world just on a phone
call or a Skype, I can dial-in,

00:46:30.020 --> 00:46:32.022 align:middle line:90%
like a canary in the coal mine.

00:46:32.022 --> 00:46:32.923 align:middle line:90%
So go alone.

00:46:32.923 --> 00:46:35.826 align:middle line:90%
It was hugely healing for me.

00:46:35.826 --> 00:46:37.161 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Oh, there's
that new one.

00:46:37.161 --> 00:46:40.497 align:middle line:84%
So for people who are
watching this and curious

00:46:40.497 --> 00:46:42.666 align:middle line:84%
about doing this, and maybe
thinking about doing it

00:46:42.666 --> 00:46:45.202 align:middle line:84%
on their own, would you
recommend to go alone?

00:46:45.202 --> 00:46:48.272 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: I would recommend
if you really do need to go

00:46:48.272 --> 00:46:50.541 align:middle line:84%
with someone or feel like
you don't want to go quite

00:46:50.541 --> 00:46:56.547 align:middle line:84%
that adventurous, at least
walking during the day,

00:46:56.547 --> 00:46:57.748 align:middle line:90%
walk alone.

00:46:57.748 --> 00:47:02.052 align:middle line:84%
Meet up at night, or walk
a good part of it alone

00:47:02.052 --> 00:47:05.189 align:middle line:84%
where you're not just
talking and staying

00:47:05.189 --> 00:47:09.793 align:middle line:90%
in your same mental frequency.

00:47:09.793 --> 00:47:14.731 align:middle line:84%
You'll miss something, and I did
have the company in the evenings

00:47:14.731 --> 00:47:15.899 align:middle line:90%
of other pilgrims, and some

00:47:15.899 --> 00:47:18.068 align:middle line:84%
of them had a very
different experience.

00:47:18.068 --> 00:47:21.071 align:middle line:84%
There were people drink
their way across, you know,

00:47:21.071 --> 00:47:23.407 align:middle line:84%
and they had a very
different Camino.

00:47:23.407 --> 00:47:25.976 align:middle line:84%
There were people went in
groups and argued and fought.

00:47:25.976 --> 00:47:28.812 align:middle line:84%
They had a very different
Camino.

00:47:28.812 --> 00:47:33.450 align:middle line:84%
You can create the quality
of Camino of your pilgrimage.

00:47:33.450 --> 00:47:37.688 align:middle line:84%
I had a beautiful experience
because of that quiet.

00:47:37.688 --> 00:47:38.922 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Amazing.

00:47:38.922 --> 00:47:40.991 align:middle line:84%
Well, did you create alters
for yourself out there,

00:47:40.991 --> 00:47:42.693 align:middle line:84%
because I know you teach
a lot about alters.

00:47:42.693 --> 00:47:44.061 align:middle line:90%
Did carry one with you?

00:47:44.061 --> 00:47:45.162 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: I did.

00:47:45.162 --> 00:47:48.031 align:middle line:84%
I do carry an altar
with me and, you know,

00:47:48.031 --> 00:47:52.469 align:middle line:84%
there's churches along the way
that are from medieval times,

00:47:52.469 --> 00:47:54.538 align:middle line:90%
and they are so incredible,

00:47:54.538 --> 00:47:57.441 align:middle line:84%
so I got to see these
beautiful alters.

00:47:57.441 --> 00:48:01.111 align:middle line:84%
And an interesting thing
is in the Catholic Church,

00:48:01.111 --> 00:48:03.513 align:middle line:84%
there's mostly the
Jesus on the cross,

00:48:03.513 --> 00:48:07.084 align:middle line:84%
but in these churches it was
always Mary holding the Christ.

00:48:07.084 --> 00:48:12.289 align:middle line:84%
It was very feminine and very
nurturing and very beautiful,

00:48:12.289 --> 00:48:13.423 align:middle line:90%
and that surprised me.

00:48:13.423 --> 00:48:16.326 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Yeah, that's a
wonderful distinction.

00:48:16.326 --> 00:48:17.561 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: And
there are places

00:48:17.561 --> 00:48:20.397 align:middle line:84%
where people created
alters with stones,

00:48:20.397 --> 00:48:22.933 align:middle line:84%
so I tried to create an
altar pretty much every day,

00:48:22.933 --> 00:48:26.637 align:middle line:84%
and prayed every day,
and listened every day.

00:48:26.637 --> 00:48:29.740 align:middle line:84%
But I also have a little
altar that I take with me,

00:48:29.740 --> 00:48:33.143 align:middle line:84%
and in it I have my
pictures of my family,

00:48:33.143 --> 00:48:37.481 align:middle line:84%
and I have found some
talismans from my life,

00:48:37.481 --> 00:48:40.150 align:middle line:84%
something from India
which is very dear to me,

00:48:40.150 --> 00:48:43.520 align:middle line:84%
and some of my rosaries
from a childhood.

00:48:43.520 --> 00:48:45.422 align:middle line:84%
And I have a prayer
book I've always carried

00:48:45.422 --> 00:48:49.026 align:middle line:84%
and write my own prayers,
and I carry Gumby.

00:48:49.026 --> 00:48:52.829 align:middle line:84%
Gumby's my totem, my joy
guide, so Gumby was part of --

00:48:52.829 --> 00:48:55.532 align:middle line:84%
Gumby rode with me on my
backpack right in the front.

00:48:55.532 --> 00:48:56.166 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: [Laughter] Oh, did he?

00:48:56.166 --> 00:48:56.867 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Yes.

00:48:56.867 --> 00:48:57.601 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: That's great.

00:48:57.601 --> 00:48:58.535 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: So, yes.

00:48:58.535 --> 00:49:01.672 align:middle line:90%
Alters are portals...

00:49:01.672 --> 00:49:02.706 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh.

00:49:02.706 --> 00:49:04.941 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: ...to
the subtle realms,

00:49:04.941 --> 00:49:06.376 align:middle line:84%
and that's why they're
so powerful.

00:49:06.376 --> 00:49:09.479 align:middle line:84%
They take us out of our
conscious third dimensional

00:49:09.479 --> 00:49:12.816 align:middle line:84%
focus, and open us
to making contact.

00:49:12.816 --> 00:49:14.017 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: How interesting.

00:49:14.017 --> 00:49:15.352 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: It's a more
beautiful, subtle realm

00:49:15.352 --> 00:49:18.689 align:middle line:84%
so that are available that
want to make contact with us.

00:49:18.689 --> 00:49:20.357 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: I'd love to learn how
to use them a little bit more.

00:49:20.357 --> 00:49:22.159 align:middle line:84%
There's a video here I
want you to take a look

00:49:22.159 --> 00:49:23.560 align:middle line:84%
at that Sonia talks
about alters,

00:49:23.560 --> 00:49:29.132 align:middle line:84%
and then we'll find
out how to use them.

00:49:29.132 --> 00:49:31.735 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Hi, I'm Sonia
Choquette, and I'm here today

00:49:31.735 --> 00:49:34.805 align:middle line:84%
to share with you the
importance and the richness

00:49:34.805 --> 00:49:37.341 align:middle line:90%
of creating a personal altar.

00:49:37.341 --> 00:49:40.944 align:middle line:84%
Just like alters are the focal
point for spiritual contact

00:49:40.944 --> 00:49:45.749 align:middle line:84%
in churches and mosques
and temples, they also have

00:49:45.749 --> 00:49:49.920 align:middle line:84%
that same value for you if
you bring one into your home.

00:49:49.920 --> 00:49:54.858 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, alters were in
people's homes over many,

00:49:54.858 --> 00:49:58.528 align:middle line:84%
many millennia and in most
parts of the world today.

00:49:58.528 --> 00:50:01.665 align:middle line:90%
So it's not an unusual thing.

00:50:01.665 --> 00:50:03.500 align:middle line:90%
To create an alter is simple.

00:50:03.500 --> 00:50:07.371 align:middle line:84%
All you need to do is
bring together the things

00:50:07.371 --> 00:50:10.741 align:middle line:84%
that uplift your heart
and help you make contact

00:50:10.741 --> 00:50:14.378 align:middle line:84%
with your divine nature,
with God, with source,

00:50:14.378 --> 00:50:18.348 align:middle line:84%
with spirit guides, with
whatever opens and expands

00:50:18.348 --> 00:50:23.153 align:middle line:84%
and helps you feel your
greater connection with life.

00:50:23.153 --> 00:50:26.156 align:middle line:84%
This is my Catholic altar
because I was raised Catholic

00:50:26.156 --> 00:50:31.361 align:middle line:84%
and I still have a lot of real
deep connection with that.

00:50:31.361 --> 00:50:33.663 align:middle line:90%
This is my Buddhist altar.

00:50:33.663 --> 00:50:35.999 align:middle line:90%
This is around the Goddess Tara,

00:50:35.999 --> 00:50:40.771 align:middle line:84%
and around this alter I have
collected Mollison prayer beads

00:50:40.771 --> 00:50:44.775 align:middle line:84%
from around the world, and so
I'll sit in front of this alter

00:50:44.775 --> 00:50:48.578 align:middle line:84%
and use them to pray
and meditate.

00:50:48.578 --> 00:50:51.348 align:middle line:84%
Back here I have a little
tiny altar that's full

00:50:51.348 --> 00:50:56.086 align:middle line:84%
of little Indian gods, and a
stone that was very special

00:50:56.086 --> 00:50:58.922 align:middle line:84%
to me that I collected
on my travels.

00:50:58.922 --> 00:51:01.558 align:middle line:84%
And make it small
because it doesn't have

00:51:01.558 --> 00:51:03.827 align:middle line:84%
to be a big deal
to create an altar.

00:51:03.827 --> 00:51:07.831 align:middle line:84%
You just bring together some
things that lift you up.

00:51:07.831 --> 00:51:10.333 align:middle line:84%
I even made an alter
once on a napkin

00:51:10.333 --> 00:51:12.969 align:middle line:84%
as I traveled just
putting flowers and petals

00:51:12.969 --> 00:51:15.105 align:middle line:90%
and pictures of people I love.

00:51:15.105 --> 00:51:20.210 align:middle line:84%
So whatever works for you, the
idea is that it's a focal point

00:51:20.210 --> 00:51:26.016 align:middle line:84%
where you can make contact with
God, with a source, with spirit,

00:51:26.016 --> 00:51:28.452 align:middle line:84%
with your heart, and
all good things in life,

00:51:28.452 --> 00:51:32.155 align:middle line:84%
and it's a very enriching
thing to create

00:51:32.155 --> 00:51:34.090 align:middle line:90%
and visit in your home.

00:51:34.090 --> 00:51:38.295 align:middle line:84%
So I hope you do that, and
I wish you all my love.

00:51:40.630 --> 00:51:42.466 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: So how do we do that?

00:51:42.466 --> 00:51:45.268 align:middle line:84%
Do you invoke different
types of energies,

00:51:45.268 --> 00:51:46.570 align:middle line:90%
or you just look at the altar?

00:51:46.570 --> 00:51:47.404 align:middle line:90%
How do you do that?

00:51:47.404 --> 00:51:48.371 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Well, you know,

00:51:48.371 --> 00:51:50.907 align:middle line:84%
an invocation is
actually to call in.

00:51:50.907 --> 00:51:52.042 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Okay.

00:51:52.042 --> 00:51:54.344 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: So you sit
down and you just call

00:51:54.344 --> 00:51:58.548 align:middle line:84%
in whatever your
spiritual construct is.

00:51:58.548 --> 00:52:02.352 align:middle line:84%
If it's, you know, Allah,
or God, or Mother Mary,

00:52:02.352 --> 00:52:03.186 align:middle line:90%
or your higher self.

00:52:03.186 --> 00:52:04.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: The guides or whatever.

00:52:04.120 --> 00:52:05.655 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Or
guides, whatever.

00:52:05.655 --> 00:52:08.124 align:middle line:84%
What you're really doing
is you're actually shifting

00:52:08.124 --> 00:52:11.862 align:middle line:84%
out of your left brain into
your heart and opening to being,

00:52:11.862 --> 00:52:16.299 align:middle line:84%
to making contact,
to say influence me,

00:52:16.299 --> 00:52:18.869 align:middle line:84%
and your reaching
at the same time.

00:52:18.869 --> 00:52:21.238 align:middle line:84%
You know, if you think
of that Sistine Chapel,

00:52:21.238 --> 00:52:24.574 align:middle line:84%
Michelangelo touching the hand
of God, that's kind of like

00:52:24.574 --> 00:52:27.310 align:middle line:84%
when you work with your
alter, you're just reaching

00:52:27.310 --> 00:52:30.247 align:middle line:84%
for the higher self
to reach you.

00:52:30.247 --> 00:52:31.848 align:middle line:90%
And you can sit for a minute.

00:52:31.848 --> 00:52:34.885 align:middle line:84%
You can light a candle, a
little water, just a prayer,

00:52:34.885 --> 00:52:36.419 align:middle line:90%
just put your hand there.

00:52:36.419 --> 00:52:38.321 align:middle line:90%
It can be as long or short.

00:52:38.321 --> 00:52:39.923 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: If you're,
say, not feeling well

00:52:39.923 --> 00:52:43.326 align:middle line:84%
or you have an illness or
something, do you use those?

00:52:43.326 --> 00:52:46.096 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: I would
say light a candle there.

00:52:46.096 --> 00:52:49.232 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it did say I need
some help, and just sit,

00:52:49.232 --> 00:52:52.736 align:middle line:84%
just pause for a moment
because it just opens you

00:52:52.736 --> 00:52:54.671 align:middle line:84%
to a different dimension
of frequency.

00:52:54.671 --> 00:52:56.473 align:middle line:84%
That would be a great
thing, or if you need help,

00:52:56.473 --> 00:52:59.743 align:middle line:84%
if you're afraid of something
or a special request,

00:52:59.743 --> 00:53:02.379 align:middle line:84%
or you need some more
confidence or assistance,

00:53:02.379 --> 00:53:05.282 align:middle line:84%
or you're confused and
you want some clarity.

00:53:05.282 --> 00:53:06.550 align:middle line:90%
Whatever.

00:53:06.550 --> 00:53:08.985 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Did you get sick
at all on the pilgrimage?

00:53:08.985 --> 00:53:12.088 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Well, because it
rained and it was just so cold

00:53:12.088 --> 00:53:14.758 align:middle line:84%
that there was illness
to the pilgrimage,

00:53:14.758 --> 00:53:19.195 align:middle line:84%
and I got strep throat,
and I got pretty sick.

00:53:19.195 --> 00:53:23.667 align:middle line:84%
I was really suffering
for a couple of days,

00:53:23.667 --> 00:53:25.435 align:middle line:90%
and I knew I was going down.

00:53:25.435 --> 00:53:30.006 align:middle line:84%
I knew I was going down,
and so I ended up going

00:53:30.006 --> 00:53:33.410 align:middle line:84%
to a little infirmary that
they have occasionally,

00:53:33.410 --> 00:53:36.813 align:middle line:84%
not in every town, but
occasionally for pilgrims.

00:53:36.813 --> 00:53:39.749 align:middle line:84%
And I went in and this
beautiful woman helped me,

00:53:39.749 --> 00:53:43.720 align:middle line:84%
and she gave me some medication,
and the pharmacy was open

00:53:43.720 --> 00:53:46.389 align:middle line:84%
on Sunday for two
hours, so I got it.

00:53:46.389 --> 00:53:50.994 align:middle line:84%
And I did suffer a few more
days, but after about five days,

00:53:50.994 --> 00:53:52.762 align:middle line:90%
it started the lift again, so.

00:53:52.762 --> 00:53:53.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: You had a fever?

00:53:53.930 --> 00:53:55.365 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: A terrible fever.

00:53:55.365 --> 00:53:56.199 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: And you walked?

00:53:56.199 --> 00:53:57.133 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: I was delusional.

00:53:57.133 --> 00:53:59.402 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: You kept
walking with it?

00:53:59.402 --> 00:53:59.903 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Yeah.

00:53:59.903 --> 00:54:01.004 align:middle line:90%
Had to.

00:54:01.004 --> 00:54:03.073 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Had to because
you had to finish it

00:54:03.073 --> 00:54:04.474 align:middle line:90%
in a certain amount of days?

00:54:04.474 --> 00:54:05.942 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: I had to finish
it in a certain amount of days

00:54:05.942 --> 00:54:07.644 align:middle line:84%
because I had to
teach in Vienna.

00:54:07.644 --> 00:54:09.145 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh, oh.

00:54:09.145 --> 00:54:09.846 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Yeah.

00:54:09.846 --> 00:54:10.981 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: I see, yeah.

00:54:10.981 --> 00:54:11.681 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Yeah, I
had this period of time.

00:54:11.681 --> 00:54:13.583 align:middle line:90%
I had to keep walking.

00:54:13.583 --> 00:54:15.652 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Did you set that
up for yourself on purpose?

00:54:15.652 --> 00:54:17.020 align:middle line:90%
Or you wouldn't have known.

00:54:17.020 --> 00:54:18.755 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Well, I think
the fever helped burn off some

00:54:18.755 --> 00:54:22.826 align:middle line:84%
of the, you know, muck
I needed to burn off,

00:54:22.826 --> 00:54:26.329 align:middle line:84%
and maybe there was a
little past life, you know,

00:54:26.329 --> 00:54:28.598 align:middle line:84%
burn it this day going
on there as well.

00:54:28.598 --> 00:54:29.532 align:middle line:90%
Who knows.

00:54:29.532 --> 00:54:30.500 align:middle line:84%
I kind of think it
was [laughter].

00:54:30.500 --> 00:54:32.002 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow, wow.

00:54:32.002 --> 00:54:33.103 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: It was

00:54:33.103 --> 00:54:35.505 align:middle line:84%
like a spiritual tour
on steroids for me.

00:54:35.505 --> 00:54:36.873 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:54:36.873 --> 00:54:40.010 align:middle line:84%
Well I can tell it's deepened
your teachings so much more,

00:54:40.010 --> 00:54:42.278 align:middle line:84%
so let's talk about some
of the teachings and some

00:54:42.278 --> 00:54:44.314 align:middle line:90%
of the practices that you use.

00:54:44.314 --> 00:54:48.118 align:middle line:84%
What can you teach us to
use during time of sickness

00:54:48.118 --> 00:54:49.486 align:middle line:90%
or breathing or anything?

00:54:49.486 --> 00:54:51.821 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Well, I'd like
to just give you a quick tool

00:54:51.821 --> 00:54:54.157 align:middle line:84%
that will help you make
contact with your higher self

00:54:54.157 --> 00:54:55.592 align:middle line:84%
and your guides,
and it is something

00:54:55.592 --> 00:54:56.793 align:middle line:90%
that we don't give ourselves.

00:54:56.793 --> 00:54:58.228 align:middle line:90%
It's called room to breathe.

00:54:58.228 --> 00:55:01.031 align:middle line:84%
And the first thing I'll
have you do is just --

00:55:01.031 --> 00:55:05.468 align:middle line:84%
I ask everybody, look, just feel
all the energy that's troubling

00:55:05.468 --> 00:55:10.674 align:middle line:84%
you, pulling on you, tugging on
you, scaring you, when you want,

00:55:10.674 --> 00:55:13.810 align:middle line:84%
excited about, whatever, and
notice that you hold it...

00:55:13.810 --> 00:55:14.878 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Okay.

00:55:14.878 --> 00:55:15.979 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: ...in
your consciousness.

00:55:15.979 --> 00:55:17.580 align:middle line:84%
Put your tongue on the
roof of your mouth,

00:55:17.580 --> 00:55:21.484 align:middle line:84%
and exhale like you're
blowing out a birthday candle.

00:55:23.453 --> 00:55:27.323 align:middle line:84%
Completely emptying the lungs
and breathe in through the nose,

00:55:27.323 --> 00:55:30.193 align:middle line:84%
but clear into your belly,
clear into your tailbone,

00:55:30.193 --> 00:55:32.962 align:middle line:84%
and then when you let
out the sound "ah,"

00:55:32.962 --> 00:55:35.265 align:middle line:84%
open it up to hear
it click in the jaw.

00:55:35.265 --> 00:55:35.899 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Ah.

00:55:35.899 --> 00:55:36.866 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Ah.

00:55:36.866 --> 00:55:40.003 align:middle line:84%
And allow the energy
to travel filled

00:55:40.003 --> 00:55:42.839 align:middle line:84%
with your own spirit
from the inside out.

00:55:42.839 --> 00:55:47.577 align:middle line:84%
Allow it to travel above you
and below you, to the north,

00:55:47.577 --> 00:55:52.449 align:middle line:84%
the south, the east and the
west, in all six directions,

00:55:52.449 --> 00:55:56.186 align:middle line:84%
pushing out everything that
is not you, not of you,

00:55:56.186 --> 00:55:58.922 align:middle line:84%
not of your beautiful
spirit, and doesn't serve you.

00:55:58.922 --> 00:56:04.494 align:middle line:84%
Do this two or three times, and
it creates an energetic room

00:56:04.494 --> 00:56:08.031 align:middle line:84%
to breathe, so you're
in the clear space,

00:56:08.031 --> 00:56:13.269 align:middle line:84%
and in that space your mind
is quiet, you can begin to get

00:56:13.269 --> 00:56:16.272 align:middle line:84%
in touch with your deeper truth
and your more authentic self.

00:56:16.272 --> 00:56:19.275 align:middle line:84%
And in that space, just
put your hand on your heart

00:56:19.275 --> 00:56:21.044 align:middle line:90%
and you can get guidance.

00:56:21.044 --> 00:56:23.813 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: If you're in pain or
any specific pain in your life,

00:56:23.813 --> 00:56:26.116 align:middle line:84%
is that -- that's a good idea
to get a reprieve from it?

00:56:26.116 --> 00:56:27.517 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Yeah,
you just need to step

00:56:27.517 --> 00:56:32.222 align:middle line:84%
and give yourself this
energetic room, above and below,

00:56:32.222 --> 00:56:39.229 align:middle line:84%
north and south, east, expand
and fill that space up with you.

00:56:39.229 --> 00:56:40.463 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: You get
your own little room.

00:56:40.463 --> 00:56:43.166 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Yeah, room
to breathe, and it's filled

00:56:43.166 --> 00:56:46.035 align:middle line:84%
up with you and anything
that is not you, not of you,

00:56:46.035 --> 00:56:47.771 align:middle line:84%
doesn't serve you,
doesn't honor you,

00:56:47.771 --> 00:56:51.307 align:middle line:84%
doesn't lift you
up, is moved out.

00:56:51.307 --> 00:56:53.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And is there --
are there any specific tools

00:56:53.610 --> 00:56:56.446 align:middle line:84%
that you used along the
way to really help you get

00:56:56.446 --> 00:56:59.415 align:middle line:84%
through that walking
with the fever?

00:56:59.415 --> 00:57:01.484 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Yes, and this is
a tool that will help you get

00:57:01.484 --> 00:57:02.919 align:middle line:90%
in touch with your intuition.

00:57:02.919 --> 00:57:05.188 align:middle line:84%
I've used it before and
it came in very handy,

00:57:05.188 --> 00:57:08.591 align:middle line:84%
and this is a tool I call
emptying the garbage.

00:57:08.591 --> 00:57:11.761 align:middle line:84%
The reason we can't feel our
intuition is our mind is fall

00:57:11.761 --> 00:57:13.396 align:middle line:84%
of thoughts and fears
and whatever,

00:57:13.396 --> 00:57:16.266 align:middle line:84%
and so emptying the garbage is
simply to just take a breath

00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:19.469 align:middle line:84%
and start naming what
you're afraid of.

00:57:19.469 --> 00:57:21.037 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid I won't
make the walk.

00:57:21.037 --> 00:57:24.741 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid I'll run out of
energy before there's a café

00:57:24.741 --> 00:57:26.309 align:middle line:90%
and I can get something to eat.

00:57:26.309 --> 00:57:28.511 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid that I'll
run out of water.

00:57:28.511 --> 00:57:29.813 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid I'll hurt my ankle.

00:57:29.813 --> 00:57:31.581 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid my knee
won't make it.

00:57:31.581 --> 00:57:33.583 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid the rain won't stop.

00:57:33.583 --> 00:57:36.653 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid my life
is out of control.

00:57:36.653 --> 00:57:39.722 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid I'm going lions
and tigers and bears, oh no,

00:57:39.722 --> 00:57:44.260 align:middle line:84%
you know, and eventually,
you're quiet.

00:57:44.260 --> 00:57:47.030 align:middle line:84%
Eventually you've
just emptied all that,

00:57:47.030 --> 00:57:49.098 align:middle line:84%
and then you take a breath,
and I would take a breath

00:57:49.098 --> 00:57:52.035 align:middle line:90%
and I'd say in my spirits, yes.

00:57:52.035 --> 00:57:55.271 align:middle line:84%
And the guidance would say,
you're going to be okay,

00:57:55.271 --> 00:57:57.674 align:middle line:84%
and I would get guidance,
and I would get healing,

00:57:57.674 --> 00:57:58.708 align:middle line:90%
and I would get thoughts.

00:57:58.708 --> 00:58:01.110 align:middle line:84%
And this is a tool
I taught for years.

00:58:01.110 --> 00:58:04.681 align:middle line:84%
It will always get you in
touch with your intuition.

00:58:04.681 --> 00:58:08.284 align:middle line:84%
It's not fear that
causes our problems.

00:58:08.284 --> 00:58:09.652 align:middle line:84%
Human beings will
always have fear.

00:58:09.652 --> 00:58:11.821 align:middle line:90%
We'll never not have fear.

00:58:11.821 --> 00:58:14.691 align:middle line:90%
It's hiding fear, stuffing fear.

00:58:14.691 --> 00:58:15.992 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah, ignoring fear.

00:58:15.992 --> 00:58:17.827 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Managing, and
pretending it's not there

00:58:17.827 --> 00:58:20.563 align:middle line:84%
that takes us away
from our higher self.

00:58:20.563 --> 00:58:22.065 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So you said something
really important there.

00:58:22.065 --> 00:58:24.067 align:middle line:84%
You said, "And my
guidance says."

00:58:24.067 --> 00:58:25.335 align:middle line:90%
>> Choquette: Yes.

00:58:25.335 --> 00:58:29.205 align:middle line:84%
My hand on my heart, then
I give my guidance voice.

00:58:29.205 --> 00:58:33.142 align:middle line:84%
My guidance says, and
see what comes up,

00:58:33.142 --> 00:58:36.412 align:middle line:84%
and when I was telling you that
story about losing my purse,

00:58:36.412 --> 00:58:40.316 align:middle line:84%
you know, my guidance
said, it'll be okay.

00:58:40.316 --> 00:58:41.518 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid I won't get it.

00:58:41.518 --> 00:58:42.719 align:middle line:84%
I don't have my passport,
I don't have a ticket,

00:58:42.719 --> 00:58:43.887 align:middle line:84%
I don't have any money,
I don't know where it is.

00:58:43.887 --> 00:58:45.021 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to
get out of here?

00:58:45.021 --> 00:58:47.290 align:middle line:84%
I don't even have a dime
to call someone to help.

00:58:47.290 --> 00:58:48.491 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: And here watching it...

00:58:48.491 --> 00:58:51.728 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: And my
guidance says take a breath,

00:58:51.728 --> 00:58:54.264 align:middle line:90%
room to breathe, it'll be okay.

00:58:54.264 --> 00:58:55.932 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And did they
show up right after that?

00:58:55.932 --> 00:58:58.368 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: Within
five minutes.

00:58:58.368 --> 00:59:00.536 align:middle line:90%
It was solved in 20.

00:59:00.536 --> 00:59:03.039 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:59:03.039 --> 00:59:05.041 align:middle line:90%
Very interesting.

00:59:05.041 --> 00:59:08.745 align:middle line:84%
Well, what a wonderful example
and inspiration that you are

00:59:08.745 --> 00:59:13.216 align:middle line:84%
to all of us to take the time
that you took in your life

00:59:13.216 --> 00:59:17.553 align:middle line:84%
as a developed teacher, to go
out and to really take that time

00:59:17.553 --> 00:59:20.023 align:middle line:90%
to deepen yourself even more.

00:59:20.023 --> 00:59:21.658 align:middle line:84%
>> Choquette: You
